y is recognized and measured at the present value of fixed payments. Renewal or early termination options are only included in the lease term if they are reasonably certain to be exercised.\n\n### 4. Impairment and Restructuring\n*   **Facilities Consolidation:** Impairment charges related to leasehold improvements and office equipment resulting from facility consolidation efforts specifically within the **AI segment** are recorded in **Restructuring charges** on the consolidated statements of operations (e.g., $36 million in 2024 and $54 million in 2023).\n*   **General Impairment:** Assets are subject to impairment if considered outside the normal course of business, though no general PP&E impairment was recorded for the AI segment in the most recent periods presented.\n\n### 5. Expense Classification (Cost of Revenue vs. R&D)\nThe company has distinct policies for how ongoing compute and data center operational costs are recognized on the income statement:\n*   **Cost of Revenue (AI Segment):** Includes infrastructure costs required to run and serve the AI models. This encompasses data center facility costs (leases, hosting, support, maintenance, energy, and bandwidth), **depreciation of servers and networking equipment**, public cloud hosting costs, and related employee compensation.\n*   **Research & Development (AI Segment):** Includes data center costs and cloud computing expenses that are directly tied to the **training of frontier AI models** (like Grok) and the development/build/testing of next-generation AI-enabled products.',
