** Satellites are depreciated over an estimated useful life of **3 to 5 years**, based on engineering studies, on-orbit performance, propellant life, and technology evolution.\n*   **Specific Classifications by Use-Case:**\n    *   **Broadband satellites:** Estimated useful life of **5 years**.\n    *   **First-generation mobile satellites:** Estimated useful life of **3 years**.\n\n**4. Generational / Technical Classification (Prospectus Summary)**\nFrom a product and operational standpoint, the company classifies its satellite constellations into specific generations based on their technical capabilities:\n*   **V1 Mobile satellites:** Currently in orbit; provide light data, SMS, and over-the-top voice services to mobile devices.\n*   **V2 Mini satellites:** Current broadband satellites providing high-speed internet to homes, businesses, and vehicles.\n*   **V2 Mobile satellites:** Next-generation mobile satellites designed for comprehensive satellite-to-mobile services (broadband data and IoT).\n*   **V3 satellites:** Next-generation Starlink broadband satellites offering 1 Tbps of downlink capacity per satellite (expected to deploy on Starship).',
